                            "raw": "{\n  \"venue_id\": 1,\n  \"name\": \"My Awesome Event\",\n  \"description\": \"This is a description of my awesome event.\",\n  \"date\": \"2025-12-25T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"time\": \"2025-12-25T18:00:00Z\",\n  \"status\": \"DRAFT\",\n  \"sales_start_date\": \"2025-12-01T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"sales_end_date\": \"2025-12-24T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"guests\": [\n    {\n      \"guest_id\": 1,\n      \"session_title\": \"Introduction to Go\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"guest_id\": 2,\n      \"session_title\": \"Building APIs with Gin\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"prices\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Presale\",\n      \"price\": 100000,\n      \"quota\": 100\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Regular\",\n      \"price\": 150000,\n      \"quota\": 200\n    }\n  ]\n}",
                            "options": {
                                "raw": {
                                    "language": "json"
                                }
                            }
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/events",
                            "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                            "path": ["events"]
                        },
                        "description": "Creates a new event.\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n1. You must be authenticated as an **organizer** or **administrator**.\n2. You must have the `venue_id` of an existing venue.\n3. You must have the `guest_id` of existing guests. You can create new guests using the \"Create Guest\" request in the \"Guests\" folder.\n\n**Request Body:**\nThe `guests` field is an array of objects, where each object contains a `guest_id` and a `session_title`.\nThe `prices` field is an array of objects, where each object contains a `name` and a `price`."
